1
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:14,633
<i> I'm sorry, son.</i>

2
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:16,500
<i> You were forced to lie.</i>

3
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:17,567
<i> Hello, Felma.</i>

4
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>I was actually planning
to surprise you,</i>

5
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,167
<i> but you're not here.</i>

6
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:21,633
<i>How many more days
are you staying there?</i>

7
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:22,433
<i> When are you coming home?</i>

8
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:24,467
<i> Oh, Manuel.</i>

9
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,500
<i> Paz is calling me.</i>

10
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:28,333
<i>She said the conference
is about to start.</i>

11
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>Let's just talk next time, okay?</i>

12
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:31,867
<i> Hurt me.</i>

13
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
<i> Just a little.</i>

14
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:34,200
<i> So when Manuel sees me,</i>

15
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:35,633
<i> maybe he'll come back.</i>

16
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:36,533
<i>- He'll come back,
- No.</i>

17
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:38,200
<i>of course,
he'll feel sorry for me.</i>

18
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>What is wrong with you?
I said, give it to me!</i>

19
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:41,900
<i> Are you really this desperate?</i>

20
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:43,667
<i> Hazel, Manuel is gone.</i>

21
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,133
<i> Do you understand?</i>

22
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:47,733
<i>He's not coming back,
he's not!</i>

23
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:49,733
<i>- Didang!
- Miss Paz!</i>

24
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,800
<i>Weren't you and Felma supposed
to have a conference</i>

25
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:52,733
<i> in Batangas?</i>

26
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:53,933
<i> What are you talking about?</i>

27
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:55,433
<i> You lied to me?</i>

28
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:56,400
<i> Hello, Jeffrey?</i>

29
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:57,367
<i> Noah?</i>

30
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:58,367
<i> Why do you have Felma's phone?</i>

31
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,900
<i>Manuel, please don't be mad
at them.</i>

32
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,433
<i>But why?
What's really going on?</i>

33
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:03,267
<i> Where are you exactly?</i>

34
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,567
<i> I'm here in Davao.</i>

35
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,900
<i> He's going to introduce me...</i>

36
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:09,733
<i>to a prospective investor
for the business.</i>

37
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,400
<i> We're meeting them.</i>

38
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:13,733
<i>Do you think Manuel
believed your alibi?</i>

39
00:01:13,867 --> 00:01:14,733
<i> I hope so.</i>

40
00:01:14,867 --> 00:01:17,700
<i>I'm not ready to tell him
the truth yet.</i>

41
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,633
<i> But isn't it really strange?</i>

42
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,333
<i> Auntie, mom never mentioned</i>

43
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:23,733
<i>any possible investor
in Davao, right?</i>

44
00:01:23,867 --> 00:01:25,367
<i> It all feels so sudden.</i>

45
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:26,933
<i>- Bro...
- Oh?</i>

46
00:01:27,067 --> 00:01:28,433
<i> Come with me to Davao.</i>

47
00:01:28,567 --> 00:01:30,600
<i>- What?
- Let's go see Felma.</i>

48
00:01:43,933 --> 00:01:45,233
Noah?

49
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,567
Are you okay?

50
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:52,367
Miss Lucy...

51
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,067
Actually, not really.

52
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:59,533
It feels good knowing...

53
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:02,100
Felma appreciates my presence.

54
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,100
But I need to watch myself.

55
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:10,533
Because you might
fall for her again?

56
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,900
Because I might start hoping
again that she'll love me.

57
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,133
Happy family?

58
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:43,200
More like hashtag
illegitimate child.

59
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,400
Dad...

60
00:02:58,533 --> 00:02:59,933
Why do you still have
to go there?

61
00:03:00,067 --> 00:03:02,067
Mom's coming home
in a couple of days anyway.

62
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:05,667
Why does it feel like you don't
want me to follow your mom?

63
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,933
I just don't want things to blow
up between you and Uncle Noah.

64
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:11,700
Dad, even if you don't say it,
I know you're jealous.

65
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:15,400
Son, you can't really blame me.

66
00:03:15,533 --> 00:03:17,833
The longer she's with that man,

67
00:03:17,967 --> 00:03:19,800
the higher the chance
I might lose her.

68
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,567
Dad, that's not true.

69
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,367
They're just friends.

70
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:27,200
I can't let my guard down.

71
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,133
I'm married.

72
00:03:29,267 --> 00:03:31,367
Noah's single.

73
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:34,600
Dad, didn't mom promise you

74
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:37,033
that you're the only one
she loves?

75
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:39,100
Dad, don't you trust mom?

76
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:44,000
Jeff, I trust your mom
completely.

77
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:45,200
But Noah? Sorry.

78
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:48,633
I know he's good to you,
but I don't fully trust him.

79
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:13,767
Perfect timing.

80
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:17,133
I was about to call you
for dinner.

81
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,433
Where's Noah?

82
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:23,700
He just stepped out for a bit.

83
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,100
Go ahead and eat first.

84
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:26,333
Come on.

85
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:27,900
Thank you.

86
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,533
I'll just wait for him.

87
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:37,367
He likes that.

88
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,167
He likes eating with you.

89
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:43,267
You know, you make him happy.

90
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,733
He's so different
when he's with you.

91
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,133
His face lights up.

92
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:51,633
His eyes shine.

93
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:56,133
He looked so different
when he came home that time...

94
00:04:57,467 --> 00:05:00,967
when you decided not to go
through with the wedding.

95
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:05,433
I'll admit, I was angry
at you then.

96
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:07,200
I told myself,

97
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:11,000
Who is this woman
who hurt my precious one?

98
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:13,400
Noah didn't deserve that.

99
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:18,467
I know.

100
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:22,167
And that hurt me, too.

101
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,833
But mostly...

102
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:30,200
Noah deserves honesty from me
more than anything.

103
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:37,600
I don't deserve someone
like him, but...

104
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:39,767
he's always there.

105
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,667
Always helping me.

106
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:48,600
I'll always be grateful
for that.

107
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:54,500
Now I understand why Noah
fell in love with you.

108
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:02,567
I just hope you can give him
even a little bit of love.

109
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:07,000
I do love him.

110
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,633
As a friend.

111
00:06:15,767 --> 00:06:17,467
Don't get mad, okay?

112
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:24,867
But if Manuel
didn't come back...

113
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,067
do you think you and Noah
would end up together?

114
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,600
Would your wedding happen?

115
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,800
- Sir Manuel.
- Hey.

116
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:45,033
Bring me a souvenier.

117
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:46,167
All right.

118
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:51,533
Dad, take care over there, okay?

119
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:52,600
You, too, kids.

120
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:54,167
Remember what I told you.

121
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,600
And don't tell your mom
that I'm coming to see her.

122
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,433
It'll ruin the surprise.

123
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:00,967
Of course, Dad.

124
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:03,133
And I'm sure mom
will be so happy

125
00:07:03,267 --> 00:07:05,567
when she sees you
walking again.

126
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,900
Come on, come on. You might be
late for your flight, Dad.

127
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:10,833
- Let's go.
- Uncle, you take care, okay?

128
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:12,967
- Yes, I'll look after your dad.
- Take care of dad.

129
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,900
I've got him.

130
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:16,100
- Uncle.
- Yes, I'll join them.

131
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:18,500
- Go on in there.
- No.

132
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:20,833
If you go with them,
don't come back, Jeff.

133
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:22,133
What? You're really
like that?

134
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:23,767
You're such a bad person.

135
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:26,500
- Okay, we'll take care.
- I'll be waiting for you.

136
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:28,300
Don't bother, Jeff.

137
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:29,933
- What?
- Just take care of dad.

138
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:31,900
What? Bye.

139
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,633
Andrea...

140
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:57,800
Was it really right
to let dad go?

141
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,067
Did we even have a choice?

142
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:03,033
Could we have stopped him?

143
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:06,967
Andrea, why do we feel guilty
for mom anyway?

144
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:09,667
She didn't do
anything wrong, right?

145
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,667
She and Uncle Noah
are just friends.

146
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,833
That's exactly it.

147
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:14,600
They're just friends,

148
00:08:14,733 --> 00:08:17,000
yet she went with him alone.

149
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,433
And so suddenly.

150
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:25,467
Even if it's for business,

151
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:28,333
mom still shouldn't
have gone with him.

152
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:33,433
She knows dad gets jealous
of Uncle Noah.

153
00:08:33,567 --> 00:08:36,033
I really don't understand,
I really don't get it.

154
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:38,567
Okay, before you two
start overthinking,

155
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,933
go inside, now.

156
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,000
I'll lock up.

157
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:43,100
Go on, come in.

158
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:44,733
Stop talking about that, right?

159
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:46,600
Forget it for now.

160
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:53,267
Oh, there.

161
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,700
We're going to Davao.

162
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:55,933
Bro, let's take a selfie first.

163
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:56,767
What?

164
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:57,933
Bro, later.

165
00:08:58,067 --> 00:08:59,267
- Yes.
- Come on.

166
00:09:00,267 --> 00:09:01,233
Come on.

167
00:09:07,967 --> 00:09:08,867
What's this?

168
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,333
Friend.

169
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:12,367
- Oh?
- Look at this.

170
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,200
What is it?

171
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,467
This.

172
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:26,333
Cheaters.

173
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:27,767
Where do you think
they're going?

174
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,167
Probably on a honeymoon.

175
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,067
With Abel?

176
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,367
Of course,
he's just driving them.

177
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:39,933
I can't believe
that Flirty Felma.

178
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:41,667
She really couldn't
control herself.

179
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,500
Dragging my husband everywhere.

180
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:46,333
No shame at all.

181
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:56,967
Ma'am Felma, please answer me.

182
00:09:58,433 --> 00:10:00,500
Ma'am Felma.

183
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:02,200
Come on.

184
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:04,433
You're so busy, Ma'am Felma.

185
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:05,900
- Didang.
- Goodness gracious!

186
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:07,133
What?

187
00:10:07,267 --> 00:10:11,400
Andrea, what are you doing?
Why are you scaring me?

188
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:13,333
Why are you calling mom?

189
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:15,300
Hey, how did you know?

190
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:17,733
I'm not calling
Ma'am Felma, why?

191
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,267
I heard you clearly.

192
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,800
You said,
"Ma'am Felma, please pick up."

193
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:24,067
- Why?
- Did I really say that?

194
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,767
- Yes.
- No, no, I didn't...

195
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:29,767
I know why you want
to talk to mom.

196
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:33,167
You're going to tell her that
dad's coming to see her, right?

197
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:35,100
Hey, no! Why would I?

198
00:10:35,267 --> 00:10:37,333
Then why? Why?

199
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:39,500
Why are you calling her?

200
00:10:41,633 --> 00:10:42,900
I just want to make sure

201
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:46,000
Sir Noah isn't making
any moves on her.

202
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:47,767
You know that

203
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:51,233
Sir Manuel is the only one
I want for Ma'am Felma.

204
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,667
Team Manuel, all the way!

205
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:56,567
All the way.

206
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,033
Yes.

207
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,133
You know what, Didang,

208
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:00,700
- Oh?
- you're something else.

209
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,267
- Hey, no, I'm not.
- Since day one,

210
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,767
you've been like that
since day one.

211
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:04,967
- I know you too well.
- Don't think ill of me.

212
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,833
Hey, Andrea.

213
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:21,833
Where's our ride?

214
00:11:21,967 --> 00:11:22,800
You're so excited, Bro.

215
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:24,733
Hold on, I'm still booking it.

216
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,067
What's Noah's address again?

217
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,733
Oh, wait.

218
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:32,067
Why Noah's house?

219
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:35,500
Didn't Felma stay at a hotel?

220
00:11:35,633 --> 00:11:36,600
Hotel?

221
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,533
Didn't she tell you?

222
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:41,000
Felma's staying at Noah's house.

223
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,200
<i>This is the address
you were looking for.</i>

224
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:04,000
<i> Yes, this is it, Bro.</i>

225
00:12:11,533 --> 00:12:12,767
Bro...

226
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,333
There, easy.

227
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,167
We'll get the bags later.

228
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:28,600
So where are we going?

229
00:12:28,733 --> 00:12:29,767
Listen.

230
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:32,300
I want to bring you
to the best spots in Davao.

231
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:33,367
But before that,

232
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:36,867
we'll have breakfast
at my friend's restaurant.

233
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,567
The food's really good there.

234
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,967
So you can relax a bit

235
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:42,500
before heading back
to Manila, right?

236
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,433
Felma? Felma?

237
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:48,233
Ma'am? Felma?

238
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:53,567
Felma?

239
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:01,067
Felma?

240
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:06,867
Manuel.

241
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:19,400
Manuel?

242
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:24,600
Oh my God!

243
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:39,200
Why didn't you tell me
you were better already?

244
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:42,600
I wanted to surprise you.

245
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,533
How did this happen?

246
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:48,967
Didn't the doctor say...

247
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:51,667
you'd never be able
to walk again?

248
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,600
I pushed myself in therapy.

249
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:57,700
I wanted to recover fast
for you and the kids.

250
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,433
He really worked hard
on his exercises, Felma.

251
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,133
Even I ended up working out.

252
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,900
Felma, this is just
the beginning.

253
00:14:10,033 --> 00:14:10,933
I promise you.

254
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:13,533
I'll do everything
to make our family happy.

255
00:14:13,667 --> 00:14:16,133
And we'll never be
separated again.

256
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:17,333
I promise.

257
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:24,400
And Hazel agreed
to separate from you?

258
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:27,500
Not yet, but I'm still
pushing through

259
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:28,567
with the annulment.

260
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,833
Does she know you're here?

261
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,533
No.

262
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:36,167
Oh no, she'll cause
more trouble.

263
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:40,300
She might take it out
on the kids.

264
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,000
Felma, don't worry.

265
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:45,433
I made sure she couldn't get
near the kids before I left.

266
00:14:56,433 --> 00:14:58,500
Ma'am, you're not allowed
in here.

267
00:14:58,633 --> 00:14:59,667
What do you mean by not allowed?

268
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:03,000
I'm sorry, Ma'am, Mr. Cruz
told me not to let you in.

269
00:15:04,967 --> 00:15:06,300
You jerk, Manuel.

270
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,367
What do you mean by not allowed?
No, I'm going in!

271
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,200
Move aside! Get out of the way!

272
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:12,733
- Ma'am.
- It can't be forbidden.

273
00:15:12,867 --> 00:15:13,867
Let me in!

274
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,600
No, Ma'am, I'm sorry.

275
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:16,867
You really can't.

276
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,567
No, my husband is in there!

277
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:19,667
How can I not be allowed?

278
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,000
- Move! I said move!
- Ma'am, please stop.

279
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:22,700
Please don't cause
trouble here, Ma'am.

280
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:23,467
- Sorry, Ma'am.
- I won't cause trouble

281
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,167
if you just let me in!

282
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,467
- Ma'am.
- What is wrong with you?

283
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,933
Ma'am, please.

284
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,100
- Leave now, I said.
- Please don't make a scene.

285
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,167
I'll call the police.

286
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,667
You're not letting me...

287
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,567
Stay right there, stay there!

288
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,200
- Ma'am, Ma'am, please stop.
- Let me in!

289
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:36,300
Ma'am.

290
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:39,767
I'll file charges against her
to shut her up.

291
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:43,233
Obstruction of justice...

292
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:46,367
is what she did conspiring
with Timo.

293
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,867
But I don't think
that would be enough.

294
00:15:51,267 --> 00:15:52,967
Hazel is obsessed with Manuel.

295
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:56,233
The only thing
that would stop her...

296
00:15:57,267 --> 00:16:00,167
is if Manuel goes back to her.

297
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:03,533
You want me to go back to her?

298
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:06,000
That's it, right?

299
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:09,433
Because the truth is,
you brought her here to Davao

300
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,967
to keep her away from me.

301
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,433
Manuel.

302
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:13,500
With all due respect,

303
00:16:13,633 --> 00:16:17,067
you have no right to talk
to Noah like that

304
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:20,400
after everything he's done
for your family.

305
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:23,333
It's not that I'm ungrateful,

306
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:25,133
but he's crossing the line.

307
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,300
This is a family problem.

308
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:27,667
He should stay out of it.

309
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:30,633
I'm sorry to say this.

310
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,033
But you're the problem, Manuel.

311
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:38,933
Hazel is only harassing Felma
because of you.

312
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:41,233
And that's what
I'm worried about.

313
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,267
Is that so?

314
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:44,667
Is that what you're telling
Felma

315
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,933
to convince her not
to get back with me?

316
00:16:47,067 --> 00:16:50,567
Manuel, stop it! Stop!

317
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:54,100
Noah has done nothing
but help me.

318
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:57,367
Hazel is the one trying
to destroy our family!

319
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,100
Felma.

320
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:08,600
Felma, what do you need?

321
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,067
She left, Ma'am, when I said
I'd call the police.

322
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:21,567
Okay, good.

323
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,033
- Thank you, Sir.
- Yes, Ma'am.

324
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,133
Take care, Ma'am.

325
00:17:24,267 --> 00:17:25,700
- Okay.
- Okay.

326
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:35,933
Andrea...

327
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:39,100
we should probably tell dad that
Hazel came back here again.

328
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:40,267
We'll do that
once they get home.

329
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,200
Call Jeffrey.

330
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:43,500
Tell him to be careful.

331
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:45,633
Hazel might storm the office.

332
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:52,133
Stop! Stop the car!

333
00:17:52,267 --> 00:17:54,267
You, get out!
Get out of there!

334
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,933
Coleen, stay here, okay?

335
00:17:59,233 --> 00:18:01,233
- What's your problem?
- Where's Manuel?

336
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:02,533
Where is Manuel?

337
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:06,667
- Let go of me!
- I saw the pictures.

338
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:07,700
Manuel was at the airport
with your mom.

339
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,600
What, are they on a honeymoon?

340
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:12,333
Hazel attacked us again, Jeff.

341
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:13,667
She blocked the road.

342
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,000
The nerve of him to do that
after he left me.

343
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:16,533
Where is your father now?
Where?

344
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:19,733
And why would I tell you? Why?

345
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:20,900
What are you talking about?

346
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,233
- Come here!
- Ouch!

347
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:23,600
Tell me!

348
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:24,767
- Let go of me!
- I told you that...

349
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:25,667
- Stop!
- Tell me!

350
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:26,267
You must tell me...

351
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,567
Let go of my sister!

352
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:37,967
That's what you deserve.

353
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:40,267
You animal!

354
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,267
- Hey!
- Let's go, Coleen.

355
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,300
Hey!

356
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:45,567
Hey!

357
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,400
You shameless people!

358
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:50,400
Hey! Come back here!

359
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:52,533
Hey!

360
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:59,233
Hey!

361
00:19:00,467 --> 00:19:01,900
Are you sure you're okay?

362
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,200
Do you want to go
to the hospital?

363
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:08,433
No.

364
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:09,700
I'm fine.

365
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:11,667
I'm just tired.

366
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,000
Felma...

367
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,633
let's go back to Manila.

368
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:18,667
The kids are waiting for you.

369
00:19:22,567 --> 00:19:24,400
You go ahead back to Manila.

370
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:35,467
Go on!

371
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:38,067
The kids need you!

372
00:19:39,167 --> 00:19:41,267
Felma, they need you, too.

373
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:43,000
Why don't you want
to go home yet?

374
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:46,700
Didn't I tell you?

375
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:49,033
Noah and I still have things
to fix here.

376
00:19:49,167 --> 00:19:50,033
What?

377
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:51,267
Investors again?

378
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,733
Yes!

379
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:55,633
We have a...

380
00:19:56,600 --> 00:20:00,100
business conference
to attend tomorrow.

381
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,567
Oh, really? Where?

382
00:20:02,733 --> 00:20:04,433
At the...

383
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:07,200
Esplanade Hotel.

384
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:08,533
Then I'll go with you.

385
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:10,733
No, you go ahead.

386
00:20:10,867 --> 00:20:12,933
I won't leave you here
with that man!

387
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:15,900
You're really crossing
the line now!

388
00:20:16,033 --> 00:20:19,800
Ma'am, maybe we can step
outside first.

389
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:21,367
Let's give them some space.

390
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:27,400
Up to now, you still think...

391
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:30,567
there's something going on
between us?

392
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:34,267
Can you blame me, Felma?

393
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,500
Fine, if this really
is business,

394
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:40,200
out of all the hotels in Davao,

395
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:42,700
why are you staying
at his house?

396
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:44,367
Don't you trust me?

397
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:46,433
I trust you,
but I don't trust him.

398
00:20:48,167 --> 00:20:50,700
How many times
do I have to tell you?

399
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,000
He's just helping me.

400
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:59,033
Manuel, Felma's not
feeling well.

401
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:00,900
Exactly.

402
00:21:01,033 --> 00:21:02,167
That's why I want
to take her with me

403
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,733
so I can take care of her!

404
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:09,867
We can't both stay here
while the kids are in Manila!

405
00:21:10,033 --> 00:21:10,900
But, Felma...

406
00:21:11,033 --> 00:21:13,500
That's enough!
Can you please just leave?

407
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,433
I already have so much
on my mind,

408
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:18,300
and you're just adding to it!

409
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:11,267
Noah.

410
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,333
Felma.

411
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,833
I'm sorry about Manuel.

412
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,667
No worries, Felma.

413
00:22:21,167 --> 00:22:23,967
If I were in Manuel's shoes...

414
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,533
I think I'll do the same.

415
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,200
I shouldn't have spoken
to him like that.

416
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:32,667
You are stressed.

417
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:34,833
I understand.

418
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,233
Noah.

419
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,400
What if...

420
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,533
this is a symptom?

421
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:47,467
What if my illness
is getting worse?

422
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:56,700
Didn't your cousin say I might
have behavioral changes?

423
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:02,133
Noah, I'm scared.

424
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,567
I'm really scared.

425
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,567
Felma.

426
00:23:09,067 --> 00:23:11,300
Let's not get ahead
of ourselves, okay?

427
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:15,400
After your biopsy...

428
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:18,700
that's when we'll really know.
